    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIf the completion items menu is very wide, the popup preview is useless.\n\n<img width=\"1290\" height=\"341\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1c3b640c-cd3f-45ad-b334-2e2489ebf452\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEither limit the width of the completion menu, or don't bother showing the popup preview when it can't reasonably be displayed.\n\nref https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/32820\n\nsince @crwebb85 gave a [lot of thought](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/29225#issuecomment-2468953172) into the completion popup preview, I wonder if that plan happens to deal with this already.",
